The paper discusses the development of a learning scheme for controlling soft microrobots based on Bayesian Optimization and Gaussian Processes. The focus is on optimizing the microrobots' locomotion performance, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of probabilistic learning and optimization techniques also suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of image analysis techniques to track the microrobots, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's emphasis on data-driven approaches and probabilistic modeling suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
